Diagnosis (
Yoshiyasu, 1987
). The species is differnent by the hindwing has a single eyespot along the submarginal fascia. In male genitalia, the species has three specialized setae about 2/3 length of valva, the third seta slightly expanded in apex. In female genitalia, the species has a pair of triangular signa, consisting of many stout spines.
